cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI, cs.IR. 

The paper proposes a new kernel-based approach for multivariate sequence classification, which is a problem that can be tackled using machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision), as these are the most relevant sub-categories for this type of work. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of kernel functions for text categorization and speech analysis, which are related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and signal processing (cs.SI), respectively, so these sub-categories are also possible.
